The legendary Seine River became the course for the athletes' procession, highlighting France's rich cultural tapestry, revolutionary essence, exceptional artisanship, and architectural legacy.

description: The Punjab and Haryana High Court has denied police protection to a couple claiming to be in a live-in relationship, citing insufficient evidence to confirm the nature of their relationship. The court stated that granting police protection in such cases could be seen as indirectly endorsing "illicit relationships." The woman, around 40, is a divorcee with children, while the man, 44, is still married with grown-up children.
title: Protection for live-in couples a tacit nod to 'illicit ties', says HC

description: Parents of the 17-year-old boy who drove a Porsche Taycan that fatally struck two bikers in Pune on May 19 could face charges of culpable homicide. Officials stated on Friday that the parents should have been aware of the risks of allowing an unlicensed minor to drive. This follows the police's submission of a 900-page chargesheet in court. Additionally, the fact that the vehicle lacked a number plate at the time of the accident further strengthens the case against the parents.
title: Cops chargesheet Porsche teen's parents for culpable homicide

description: Sharing an update on an Indian astronaut's upcoming space mission, Space Minister Jitendra Singh informed the Lok Sabha that “one Gaganyatri from ISRO will undertake space travel to the International Space Station (ISS)”. In a written reply on Wednesday, the minister stated that ISRO is "pursuing an ISRO-NASA joint mission to the ISS, where one Gaganyatri from ISRO will travel to the ISS. This collaborative effort involves ISRO, NASA, and the NASA-identified private entity Axiom Space.
title: One Gaganyaatri will undertake space travel to ISS post-Aug: Minister

description: For the first time, NASA has used laser communication technology to send 4K video streams from an aircraft to the International Space Station (ISS) and back. This achievement is part of a series of tests on new technology that could enable live video coverage of astronauts on the Moon during the US’s Artemis missions. Traditionally, NASA has relied on radio waves for space communication. Laser communications, however, use infrared light, allowing for data transmission 10 to 100 times faster than radio frequency systems.
title: Nasa streams 4k video from aircraft to international space station & back

description: Amid controversy over UP and Uttarakhand government directives concerning eateries and stalls along the Kanwar route, large white screens were placed in front of several mosques and mazars in Haridwar. Senior Uttarakhand cabinet minister Satpal Maharaj, overseeing tourism, culture, and PWD portfolios, justified the action, stating, "This has been done to avoid unnecessary excitement or provocation from any side and ensure the Kanwar Yatra runs smoothly."
title: Mosques and mazars on kanwar route in Haridwar 'covered up'

description: A mere change of five marks has brought joy to some and heartbreak to others as candidates have moved up or down by as much as 8,000 ranks in NEET-UG for medical school admissions. As reported exclusively by TOI, 17 candidates with perfect scores of 720 were declared toppers, compared to 61 when NTA first released the merit list following the Supreme Court's order.
title: Two of 17 NEET toppers from Delhi, 4 from Rajsthan

description: Defending the Agnipath scheme amid widespread criticism, PM Narendra Modi asserted on Friday that short-term recruitment of soldiers is essential to keep the armed forces young and combat-ready. He accused the opposition of misleading the youth and playing politics with national security issues. It is “necessary reform” undertaken by the military, PM Modi stressed.
title: PM Modi defends Agnipath: Will keep forces combat-ready
SIA attaches property of narco-terror accused in J&K's Poonch
Paper leak unearthed during PSIR online exam conducted by NTA in Mohali

description: India and the United States signed their first bilateral 'Cultural Property Agreement' (CPA) on Friday. This agreement aims to prevent the illegal trafficking of cultural property and ensure the retrieval of antiquities to their place of origin. It will facilitate the quick seizure of Indian antiquities at US Customs and ensure their smooth repatriation to India.
title: India, US ink pact to prevent illegal trafficking of 'cultural property', aid

description: Assam's Moidams, the mound-burial system of the Ahom dynasty, were inscribed on the UNESCO World Heritage List on Friday. This brings the number of World Heritage sites in India to 43, placing India sixth globally for the most world heritage properties. This is the third world heritage property from Assam on the list, following Kaziranga National Park and Manas Wildlife Sanctuary.
title: Moidams, Ahom dynasty’s mound-burial system, included in Unesco World Heritage List

description: Rajya Sabha erupted in uproar on Friday afternoon when Kerala MP John Brittas attempted to introduce a private member's bill. The bill aimed to make governors constitutionally bound by the advice of the state council of ministers. In a rare occurrence, the introduction of the bill was defeated as treasury benches voted against it.
title: Move to introduce private member’s bill on binding governors creates ruckus
Europe’s 1st lunar rover to fly to Moon by year-end

description: The latest SmackDown, ahead of SummerSlam 2024, features key matches and significant segments taped in Omaha, Nebraska. Find out how the wrestlers fared as they set their sights on the road to the hottest event of this summer, in an attempt to lay waste to the their competitors in the squared circle.
title: SmackDown July 26 Preview: Matches, Segments and more
Apple goes Pro in India by bringing in assembly of most-sophisticated iPhone models

description: Pakistan denied responsibility for terrorism and rejected PM Modi's warnings on Kargil Vijay Diwas. They claimed India was suppressing the fundamental rights of Kashmiris. PM Modi warned Pakistan against terrorist activities, citing India’s victory in Kargil. He emphasized India's resolve to combat terrorism. Kargil Vijay Diwas commemorates India's victory in the 1999 conflict and honors the soldiers' sacrifices.
title: On PM Modi's fresh warning, Pakistan as usual cites Kashmir
'Don't teach me ... ': Mamata hits back at MEA over B'desh refugees row

description: A 24-year-old woman from Bihar, Kriti Kumari, was brutally murdered inside her PG in Bengaluru. New CCTV footage reveals the harrowing incident where the attacker swiftly rushes towards Kriti, drags her, and stabs her multiple times. Despite her screams for help, no one intervenes. The attacker then walks away, leaving Kriti drenched in blood and collapsing against the wall.
title: B'luru murder: Chilling CCTV footage shows killer stabbing woman as she screams

description: West Bengal, led by the Trinamool Congress, and Kerala, governed by the CPM's LDF, have faced prolonged disputes with their respective governors over the delay in assent to bills passed by their legislative assemblies. The Supreme Court has now taken note of their pleas, providing hope for resolution. In earlier cases, the top court has been stringent regarding governors sitting over bills, offering a beacon of hope for these states. The Trinamool Congress-ruled West Bengal and the CPM-led LDF government in Kerala have faced prolonged stand-offs with their governors.
title: Guvs holding up bills: SC takes note of West Bengal, Kerala pleas

description: The Trump-Vance campaign faced unexpected challenges from Kamala Harris, who gained significant support among young voters. Despite a close overall race, Trump's team struggles with controversies and internal disputes, including debates about running mate JD Vance. Harris's unified Democratic backing and her portrayal of the race as 'Prosecutor v Felon' have also intensified tensions.
title: 'Fight! Fight! Fight!' meets 'Bring it on! When we fight, we win!'

description: Suryakumar Yadav and Hardik Pandya were spotted enjoying each other's company during Team India's training session in Kandy ahead of the first T20I match against Sri Lanka, scheduled to take place on Saturday.
title: Watch: Surya, Hardik's priceless connect over unique fielding drill

description: Brazil reported the world's first deaths from the Oropouche virus, transmitted by mosquitoes and midges, in Bahia. This virus, similar to dengue, has spread in South and Central Americas. It is not directly contagious and lacks specific treatments. Authorities are probing potential maternal transmission. Experts stress further research and readiness to prevent outbreaks.
title: World's first death from Oropouche virus: What we know so far

description: West Bengal Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee planned to ask Prime Minister Narendra Modi to replace Niti Aayog with the Planning Commission. She deemed Niti Aayog powerless and criticized the budget for discriminating against opposition-ruled states. Banerjee chose to attend the Niti Aayog meeting, despite the INDIA bloc's boycott, to raise concerns on a unified platform.
title: Scrap Niti Ayog, restore planning commission: Mamata Banerjee

description: Cambridge Dictionary has added 3,200 new words and phrases this week, enhancing its lexicon with internet slang terms like 'boop,' 'the ick,' 'chef's kiss,' and 'scicomm.' According to Cambridge Dictionary's publishing manager, Wendalyn Nichols, these additions hold the promise of longevity, demonstrating the natural evolution of language. The online gaming also inspired several new entries in the dictionary.
title: 'The Ick,' 'Boop' now in Cambridge Dictionary. What it means

description: On the first day of the Paris Olympics, Saturday, rower Balraj Panwar and the shooters will lead off India's participation. Additionally, the Indian men's hockey team will begin their campaign against New Zealand. The day will also feature matches in badminton, tennis, and table tennis.
title: Paris Olympics: India's full Day 1 schedule

description: Suryakumar Yadav, who has recently been named as the captain of the Indian T20I team, made a statement on Friday. He emphasized that the team will maintain the aggressive style of play that was a signature of the previous captain, Rohit Sharma's tenure. India adopted a revolutionary attacking approach starting from the ODI World Cup held in their home country last year, under Rohit's leadership. This aggressive brand of cricket continued to be the team's hallmark even after the World Cup victory in the Americas, where Rohit bid farewell to T20I cricket.
title: 'The same train will go ahead': Surya ahead of first SL T20I

description: Pune Police have filed a 900-page chargesheet in connection with a Porsche car accident that occurred on May 19 in Kalyaninagar. The incident involved a teen driver who rammed his luxury car into a bike, killing two techies around 2:30 am. The victims, both IT professionals, were on a two-wheeler when they were struck by the Porsche, reportedly driven by a minor. Initially, the Juvenile Justice Board (JJB) granted bail to the teenager, the son of a real estate developer, shortly after the incident and instructed him to write a 300-word essay on road safety.
title: Pune Police files 900-page chargesheet in Porsche car accident case

description: On its 10th anniversary, PM Modi praised the 'MyGov' platform for its role in participative governance. BJP chief JP Nadda and Minister Manohar Lal Khattar emphasized its importance in citizen-government engagement and policy-making. They commended the platform for bridging the gap between the government and the public.

description: West Bengal chief minister Mamata Banerjee, currently in the national capital for a Niti Aayog meeting, met with Delhi chief minister Arvind Kejriwal's wife, Sunita Kejriwal, on Friday. This visit comes at a time when CM Arvind Kejriwal is in Tihar jail in connection with a liquor policy case. CM Mamata is in Delhi for the Niti Aayog meeting, which she has criticised, calling for its abolition and demanding the restoration of the Planning Commission.
title: Bengal CM Mamata meets Arvind Kejriwal's wife, parents in Delhi

description: Retired Major General Vijay Joshi recounted Prime Minister Narendra Modi's visit to the Military Command Hospital in Udhampur during the 1999 Kargil War. Modi's presence uplifted soldiers' spirits and demonstrated true patriotism. Joshi appreciated Modi's personal engagement and focus on soldiers' well-being. The article also highlights the importance of Kargil Vijay Diwas, commemorating Operation Vijay's success.
title: 'Raised josh of soldiers': Retd. Major General recalls PM Modi's visit to injured soldiers during Kargil War

description: Hardik Pandya's skill sets are equivalent to premier England all-rounder and captain Ben Stokes but the mercurial Indian needs to show more consistency, reckoned former New Zealand cricketer Scott Styris.
title: 'Hardik is as skilled as Stokes, but...': Former Kiwi player

The updated results will be out within two days according to Union Education Minister Dharmendra Pradhan.

description: The women and child development minister shared concerning malnutrition data in India. In June, 17% of children under six were underweight, 36% were stunted, and 6% were wasted. Uttar Pradesh had the highest stunting rate, while wasting was most severe in Lakshadweep. Some states, like Goa, showed better results with lower malnutrition rates.
title: 1 in 2 children under 5 yrs of age malnourished: Centre
'As per wishes of PM Modi': 4 more BJP-led states announce job quotas for Agniveers

description: A Park+ survey of 500 electric vehicle owners from Delhi NCR, Mumbai, and Bangalore revealed that 88% suffered from charging anxiety, with maintenance costs and resale value also being major concerns. 51% preferred conventional vehicles. Tata Nexon EV emerged as the favorite. BYD was noted for its high pricing.
title: Over 50% Indian EV owners want to get back to petrol/diesel vehicles: Report

description: Suryakumar Yadav, India's newly appointed T20 captain, expressed his determination to avoid the pitfalls of his previous domestic captaincy as he prepares to lead the team against Sri Lanka for the first time. The 33-year-old took over the reins from the beloved Rohit Sharma, who stepped down from the 20-over format following India's triumphant World Cup campaign in June. Despite competition from all-rounder Hardik Pandya, Suryakumar secured the captaincy role, with concerns over Pandya's recurring injury absences playing a factor in the decision.

description: Gautam Gambhir's key task as India head coach will be man-management and not coaching a bunch of talented players in their respective skills, said former player and ex-chief selector Sandeep Patil on Friday.

description: India's foreign exchange reserves surged by $4 billion to reach $670.857 billion for the week ending on July 19, according to the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) on Friday. This rise follows an earlier jump of $9.699 billion, bringing the reserves to an all-time high of $666.854 billion for the week concluding on July 12.
title: India's forex reserves jump $4 bn to record high of $670.857 bn: RBI

description: The GROWTH-India telescope at the Indian Astronomical Observatory in Ladakh has captured a building-sized asteroid's closest approach to Earth. The 0.7m wide-field telescope, part of a joint venture by IIT Bombay and Indian Institute of Astrophysics, tracked the asteroid's rapid motion, making background stars look like streaks. The telescope specializes in time-domain astronomy.
title: India's 1st fully robotic telescope captures image of 'building-sized' asteroid

description: India cruised to a ten-wicket victory over Bangladesh, reaching the Asia Cup final. Renuka Singh's three wickets and Smriti Mandhana's fifty led to an easy chase of 81 runs. India now faces either Pakistan or Sri Lanka in the final.

description: Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman announced a cut in basic customs duty on mobile phones, chargers and some components as part of the Union Budget 2024. This reduction has led to lower prices for Apple iPhone models in India, particularly benefiting the high-end Pro models. Apple’s official store now reflects these updated prices.

description: Nasa announced astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore will spend extra time on the ISS due to Boeing Starliner thruster issues. Boeing is analyzing data to ensure safe return. Multiple landing dates available in August. This was Boeing's first manned test flight, unlike SpaceX, which has been flying astronauts since 2020.

description: Kremlin spokesman Dmitry Peskov noted former US President Donald Trump is not significantly different from other American political elites, who share an anti-Russian sentiment. He acknowledged that during Trump's presidency, numerous sanctions were imposed on Russia. Although he exhibited some political wisdom in maintaining dialogue, it did not substantially impact Russia-US relations.

description: In Q2 2024, Apple's market share in China fell to 14%, dropping it out of the top five vendors. Vivo leads the market, followed by Oppo, Honor, Huawei, and Xiaomi. Total smartphone shipments rose by 10%, with Huawei benefiting from its new releases.

description: The former president had initially withheld his endorsement following Joe Biden’s decision to withdraw from the campaign, favoring an open nominating contest at next month’s Democratic National Convention in Chicago. However, after Harris secured endorsements from Bill and Hillary Clinton, Nancy Pelosi, various state governors, senior Democrats in Congress, and Biden himself, Obama added his voice in a significant boost for the vice-president. The endorsement was revealed in a video released by Harris’s campaign on Friday, showing a phone call between Harris and the Obamas.

description: ​The bond between Menaka and her children was profound. description: Barack and Michelle Obama endorsed Vice President Kamala Harris for the presidential run, supporting her following President Biden's decision not to seek reelection. They have decreased the budget for jails as well. At least increase the budget for jails. You have only allocated Rs 300 crore. Now you have sent me to jail, tomorrow you will have to go to jail. The court directed the Department of Personnel and Training and the Ministry of Home Affairs to prominently display the recent memorandum lifting the ban on their websites.

description: The newly elected Mohan Majhi government in Odisha has rebranded two key schemes from the previous administration. Biju Swasthya Kalyana Yojana (BSKY) is now Gopabandhu Jan Arogya Yojana (GJAY) and is integrated with Ayushman Bharat. The Kalia cash incentive programme for farmers will be replaced by CM KISAN. Additionally, Biju Patnaik's name was removed from the free laptop distribution scheme, now named after poet Godabarisha Mishra. These changes came shortly after Majhi reversed a decision to drop Biju Patnaik's name from the state's sports award.
title: ‘Biju’ dropped as Odisha govt rebrands schemes in budget

description: Former Pakistan captain Shahid Afridi has criticized the Pakistan Cricket Board for its frequent leadership and structure changes, arguing they negatively impact the team's performance. He suggests a collaborative approach involving senior board members and experienced players to develop a long-term strategy and new systems to ensure growth and consistency in Pakistan cricket.
title: 'Things don't work this way': Shahid Afridi criticizes PCB
Indian national from Bihar charged with selling counterfeit pharmaceuticals in US

description: OpenAI has introduced SearchGPT, an AI search tool, to compete with Google. It offers timely answers with links to relevant sources. Initially, a select group of users tested SearchGPT. OpenAI collaborated with major publishers to refine the tool.
title: ChatGPT maker OpenAI to take on Google Search with this new tool

description: Jasprit Bumrah discussed the challenges faced by Mumbai Indians skipper Hardik Pandya during the 2024 IPL season. Pandya, who took over from Rohit Sharma, faced intense scrutiny and frequent booing from fans, particularly at Wankhede Stadium. The team's poor performance, finishing last in the IPL standings with only four wins in 14 matches, further exacerbated the situation.
title: 'World can think what they want...': Bumrah on Pandya's challenges in IPL

description: Heavy rain drenched New Delhi, providing relief from the humidity. The India Meteorological Department forecast more rain in the next two hours for various areas. Northern India, including Delhi, is likely to see moderate rainfall this week. In June, Delhi recorded 235.5 mm of rain in a 24-hour period, the highest in 88 years.
title: Delhi wakes up to heavy rainfall, IMD predicts more showers ahead

description: A 5-year-old boy drowned at BPTP Park Serene's pool in Gurgaon while lifeguards ignored the situation. They lacked proper training, leading to their arrest for negligence. The boy's family filed a complaint. The developer and maintenance agency face scrutiny.
title: Boy drowns in Gurgaon swimming pool; guards were 'busy on phone'

description: Former India cricketer Pragyan Ojha has announced a new era under new head coach Gautam Gambhir, who took over after India's T20 World Cup victory under Rahul Dravid. Gambhir is set to embark on his first tour and has already made significant changes, such as appointing Suryakumar Yadav as the T20I captain.
title: 'To call senior players for ODIs is...': Ex-cricketer endorses 'Gambhir era'
Mexican drug kingpin 'El Mayo' Zambada and El Chapo's son arrested in US

description: Vice President Kamala Harris urged Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu to finalize a peace deal, addressing the humanitarian crisis in Gaza. Harris called for a ceasefire and release of hostages, marking a shift from Biden’s approach. She emphasized the importance of not ignoring the suffering, signaling a proactive stance on Middle East peace efforts.
title: 'I will not be silent': Harris tells Netanyahu to ease suffering in Gaza
